SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 122
By Reeves
A RESOLUTION to honor Bud and Kay Mitchell on the occasion
of their retirement.
WHEREAS, Bud and Kay Mitchell have taken a much-deserved retirement after thirty-
eight years of serving the motoring public as the proprietors of Bud's Tire in Murfreesboro; and
WHEREAS, during that time, the Mitchells and Bud's Tire helped thousands of families
keep their vehicles properly maintained and operating safely on the road; and
WHEREAS, located at 3600 Woodbury Pike, Bud's Tire is a fixture in the Murfreesboro
community, and the business has been noted for selling the highest quality products at
reasonable prices; and
WHEREAS, throughout their ownership and management of this successful business
venture, Mr. and Mrs. Mitchell welcomed their loyal clientele with a warm, hometown feeling;
and
WHEREAS, the Mitchells always treated their customers fairly, and their word was their
bond; and
WHEREAS, Bud and Kay Mitchell are now embarking upon new adventures in their
lives, while also spending more time with their family and friends; and
WHEREAS, Bud and Kay Mitchell are most deserving of our approbation on this special
occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Bud and Kay Mitchell for thirty-eight years
of dedicated service to the vehicle owners of Murfreesboro and Rutherford County as the
